This paper discusses the power management database tool used on a supercomputer, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses benchmarking and optimization of power efficiency, which could fall under the categories of architecture (cs.AR), performance (cs.PF), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
